<div class="container">
    <h1>Admin Management Portal</h1>
    <p class="mb-4">
        Welcome to the Admin Management Portal, your central hub for overseeing and maintaining the user base of the application.
        This portal provides powerful tools for managing both administrators and trainers, ensuring a streamlined and efficient workflow
        to meet your organization's needs. Whether you’re assigning roles or updating user information,
        everything you need is just a few clicks away.
    </p>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Manage Admins</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        Access and control administrator accounts to maintain the integrity and security of the system. Add, remove, or update
                        administrator roles and permissions as needed. Ensure your team of admins has appropriate access levels to effectively manage the platform.
                    </p>
                    <a asp-area="@AdminRole" asp-controller="Manage" asp-action="ManageAdmins" class="btn btn-primary">Manage Admins</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Manage Trainers</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        Oversee and manage trainer accounts to ensure users have access to the best resources and expertise. Promote, demote, or update roles
                        for trainers, and monitor their activity to keep the platform running smoothly and efficiently.
                    </p>
                    <a asp-area="@AdminRole" asp-controller="Manage" asp-action="ManageTrainers" class="btn btn-secondary">Manage Trainers</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@section Styles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/admin-home.css" />
}